{"type":"message","id":"f392816f","parentId":"a803815f","timestamp":"2026-04-16T04:15:15.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to run my Session Startup sequence. According to AGENTS.md, I need to:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who I am\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who I'm helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nLet me check what files exist and read them. Today's date is 2026-04-16, so I should check:\n- memory/2026-04-16.md (today)\n- memory/2026-04-15.md (yesterday)\n\nFrom the Project Context, I can see:\n- SOUL.md exists and has been loaded\n- USER.md exists and has been loaded\n- MEMORY.md exists and has been loaded\n- HEARTBEAT.md exists and has been loaded\n\nThe memory files for today and yesterday may or may not exist. Let me read them.\n\nActually, looking at the context provided, SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md are already in the Project Context. But I should still follow the protocol and read them fresh, plus check for today's and yesterday's memory files.\n\nLet me read:\n1. SOUL.md\n2. USER.md\n3. memory/2026-04-16.md\n4. memory/2026-04-15.md\n5. MEMORY.md (since this is a direct chat/main session)","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read:0","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/workspace/projects/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read:1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/workspace/projects/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read:2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/workspace/projects/workspace/memory/2026-04-16.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read:3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/workspace/projects/workspace/memory/2026-04-15.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read:4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/workspace/projects/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"coze","model":"kimi-k2-5-260127","usa